1. Add DBUtils in your utilities
2. Add postgresql dependency
     <dependency>
        <groupId>org.postgresql</groupId>
        <artifactId>postgresql</artifactId>
        <version>42.2.8</version>
    </dependency>
3.Create a folder under feature : DatabaseFeatures
4.Create your feature file: day23_read.feature
5.Write your steps in the feature file
================================
Database testing is done for making sure database data is working as expected
-Check if UI data exist in database
-Check is the database tables have expected data.
-For example, when user adds money to the bank account, then does is stored in the database
-For example, when customer is created a user account, does is stored in the database
-----
Database is usually the most stable part of hte application
And database should perform well so UI can work property
For that reason database tesing is done.
------
Our database is postgresql database
